is Arnais\n* Philip Cezar\n* Freddie Hubalde\n* Vergel Meneses\n* Allan Caidic\n* Johnny Abarientos\n* Chito Loyzaga\n* Marlou Aquino\n* Eric Menk\n* Jayjay Helterbrand\n* Mark Caguioa\n|}\n{{column}}\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! style=\"{{PBA color cell|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel}}\" width=\"50%\" | PBA Scoring Champion\n! style=\"{{PBA color cell|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel}}\" width=\"50%\" | PSA Professional Cager of the Year\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* Mark Caguioa&nbsp;- 2004-05, 2006\u201307, 2010\u201311\n* Marlou Aquino - 1996\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* Mark Caguioa&nbsp;\u2013 2007, 2012\n* Jayjay Helterbrand&nbsp;\u2013 2009\n|}\n{{columns-end}}\n\n==Players of note==\n<!--Please keep the list arranged alphabetically to avoid POV issues. Thanks. -->\n\n===Members of the PBA's 25 greatest players===\n<!--Please keep the list arranged alphabetically to avoid POV issues. Thanks. -->\n* '''[[Johnny Abarrientos]]''', known as the \"Flying A\" throughout his career. Acquired by the team in 2006 when he became free agent.\n* '''[[Francis Arnaiz]]''', a glamour boy back from his days with Toyota, joined Jaworski at Ginebra and became one of the most popular players in franchise history. He retired in 1986 after three seasons with the team.\n* '''[[Allan Caidic]]''', known as \"The Trigger Man,\" he played his last season with Ginebra in 1999, before becoming team manager of the team and currently an assistant coach.\n* '''[[Philip Cezar]]''', \"The Scholar\" played his last season with the team during his celebrated 16-year PBA career.\n* '''[[Freddie Hubalde]]''', played for Ginebra during the final year of his career.\n* '''[[Robert Jaworski]]''', known as \"The Big J\" and \"Jawo.\"\n* '''[[Vergel Meneses]]''', also known as the \"Aerial Voyager,\" played for Ginebra from 1999\u20132002.\n\n===Other notable players===\n{{Main|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel all-time roster}}\n'''1979-1995:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* William Alexander\n* [[Billy Ray Bates]]\n* Jim Bradley\n* Carlos Briggs\n* John Campbell\n* Jervis Cole\n* Alex Coles\n* Ron Davis\n* Tommy Davis\n* Glen Dedmon\n* Jack Dorsey\n* Harold Driver\n* Terry Duerod\n* [[Kevin Gamble]]\n* Keith Gray\n* [[Sylvester Gray]]\n* [[Michael Hackett]]\n* Andre Hardy\n* [[Steve Hood]]\n* Anthony Hunter\n* Darryl Joe\n* Danny Jones\n* Marlin Kimbrew\n* Toney Mack\n* Antonio Madison\n* Lawrence Massey\n* Tony Massop\n* [[Wes Matthews]]\n* Darrin Mayo\n* Carlton McKinney\n* [[Larry McNeill]]\n* Isiah Morris\n* Darryl Prue\n* Brian Shorter\n* Terry Thames\n* [[Dean Tolson]]\n* Kenny Tyler\n* [[Daren Queenan]]\n* Anthony Roberts\n* Clinton Wheeler\n* Jamie Waller\n* Joe Ward\n* Dartona Washam\n* [[Mitchell Wiggins]]\n{{colend}}\n'''1996:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* Fred Cofield\n* Reggie Fox\n* [[Henry James (basketball)|Henry James]]\n* Derek Rucker\n{{colend}}\n'''1997:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n*  Andy Bostick\n* Michael Cumberland\n* Dennis Edwards\n* Tyrone Hopkins\n* [[Chris King (basketball)|Chris King]]\n* Purnell Perry\n* John Strickland\n* Leon Trimmingham\n{{colend}}\n'''1999:'''\n* Mario Donaldson\n\n'''2000:'''\n* Ryan Fletcher\n\n'''2001:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* Jarrod Gee\n* Brian Green\n* Roy Hammonds\n* Mark Jones\n{{colend}}\n'''2002:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Ben Davis (basketball)|Ben Davis]]\n* Ricky Price\n{{colend}}\n'''2003:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Rossel Ellis]]\n* George Reese\n{{colend}}\n'''2004:'''\n* [[Torraye Braggs]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2005-06:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Eddie Elisma]]\n* [[Sean Lampley]]\n* [[Chris Porter (basketball)|Chris Porter]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2007-12:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n*  Rod Nealy\n* [[Rahshon Turner]]\n*  Chris Alexander\n* [[David Noel]]\n* [[Awvee Storey]]\n* [[Mildon Ambres]]\n* [[Denham Brown]]\n* [[Chris Daniels (basketball)|Chris Daniels]]\n*  Nate Brumfield\n* [[Curtis Stinson]]\n* [[Donald Sloan (basketball)|Donald Sloan]]\n* [[Jackson Vroman]]\n* [[Cedric Bozeman]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2012-13:'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Herbert Hill (basketball)|Herbert Hill]]\n* [[Vernon Macklin]]\n* [[Dior Lowhorn]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2013-14'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Leon Rodgers]]\n* [[Josh Powell]]\n* [[Gabriel Freeman]]\n* [[Zaccheus Mason]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2014-15'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n*  Michael Dunigan\n* [[Orlando Johnson]]\n* [[Sanchir Tungalag]]\n* Kim Ji-wan\n{{colend}}\n'''2016'''\n{{colbegin|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Othyus Jeffers]]\n* [[Paul Harris (basketball)|Paul Harris]]\n* [[Justin Brownlee]]\n{{colend}}\n'''2017'''\n* Justin Brownlee\n'''2018'''\n*[[Charles Garc\u00eda]]\n* Justin Brownlee\n\n===Retired numbers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n| colspan=\"4\" style= \"background: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|1}}; color: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|2}}\" | '''Barangay Ginebra San Miguel retired numbers'''\n|-\n! width=40px style=\"background: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|3}}; color: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|4}}\" | N\u00b0\n! width=150px style=\"background: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|3}}; color: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|4}}\" |Player\n! width=40px style=\"background: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|3}}; color: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|4}}\" |Position\n! width=100px style=\"background: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|3}}; color: #{{PBA color|Barangay Ginebra San Miguel|4}}\" |Tenure\n|-\n| '''7''' || [[Robert Jaworski]] || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 1984\u20131998{{ref label|Note1|a|a}}\n|-\n| '''8''' || [[Allan Caidic]] || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 1998\u20131999{{ref label|Note2|b|b}}\n|-\n|}\n* {{note label|Note1|a|a}}&nbsp;\u2013  retired on July 8, 2012 during the semifinal round of the [[2012 PBA Governors Cup]]<ref>[http://www.interaksyon.com/interaktv/jaworski-showered-with-love-adoration-by-pba-family Jaworski showered with love, adora